Course Summary

This Math for Kids course has been assembled to help students improve their understanding of basic arithmetic, algebra and geometry. The course's fun lessons and quizzes can help your students bring up their grades, get ready for exams and reinforce the math topics they've been learning in class.

About This Course

In this course, students will review the mathematical procedures used to solve problems involving math fundamentals and number sense, fractions, and basic statistics. The course is composed of a series of chapters, each with their own lessons, transcripts and assessments. Have your students complete the lessons to improve their mathematics skills, and then have them review the lesson transcripts to reinforce their understanding of the subject matter. After each lesson, they can test the knowledge they have obtained by completing the accompanying quiz. Each chapter also has its own practice chapter exam so that you can have your student test their overall understanding of the material presented.

How It Works

  • Students can get a quick review of different mathematical procedures by completing the short and engaging lessons.
  • The lessons can be reviewed as many times as needed.
  • Lesson transcripts offer a additional review of the material that can help students improve their understanding of key math concepts.
  • The teacher tabs can connect you or your students to our professional instructors in the event you or your students develop a question about the lessons.
  • For a quick and effective way to assess your students progression, have your students complete the lesson quizzes.

Using the Course

These lessons provide students with accessible and easy-to-use resources that they can use to improve their understanding of mathematical operations. Whether your student(s) are having a hard time keeping up in class, or reviewing for a test this course will help them improve their math skills.

Parents and teachers will find that these the lessons and assessments will help their students:

  • Understand how to solve math problems on homework or assessments
  • Help students build a positive attitude about math
  • Build up confidence to participate in classroom discussions about math
  • Better understand their math teacher's instructions
